The stage winner was awarded &lt;U+20AC&gt;8,000 on a normal stage and &lt;U+20AC&gt;10,000 for a time trial. The money gradually decreases, with the 20th finisher receiving &lt;U+20AC&gt;200. The first person to cross the intermediate sprint wins &lt;U+20AC&gt;1,500. Money is also awarded for crossing the categorized climbs, for the best young rider of each stage, the most combative rider, and the best team of the stage.33

